@page "/3d-models"
@using MudBlazor

<PageTitle>3D Models</PageTitle>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Large" Class="mt-4">
    <MudStack Spacing="3">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h4">3D Models</MudText>

        <MudText>
            When creating games I make most of the assets that are needed. To do this I use different software to
            create the assets that will be used.
        </MudText>

        <MudDivider Class="my-2" />

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">Autodesk Maya</MudText>
        <MudText>
            When creating 3D models I use Autodesk Maya as I have the most experience with the software and prefer how
            it functions compared to 3DS Max. I think Maya is incredible; my main issue is its tendency to crash when
            creating and editing UV shells.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-4">3DS Max</MudText>
        <MudText>
            I have learned how to use 3DS Max, however I find Maya to be more efficient, so I rarely use Max.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-4">Photoshop</MudText>
        <MudText>
            I use Photoshop to create textures applied to my models. This stage can be tricky due to hidden polygons
            or the modelling software not playing nicely with Photoshop.
        </MudText>

        <MudDivider Class="my-4" />

        <!-- Gallery -->
        <MudGrid Spacing="3">
            <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
                <MudCard Class="gallery-card">
                    <MudCardMedia Image="images/ship.JPG" Height="280" />
                    <MudCardContent>
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Ship</MudText>
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.caption">Modelled in Maya</MudText>
                    </MudCardContent>
                </MudCard>
            </MudItem>

            <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
                <MudCard Class="gallery-card">
                    <MudCardMedia Image="images/bottle.JPG" Height="280" />
                    <MudCardContent>
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle2">Bottle</MudText>
                        <MudText Typo="Typo.caption">Modelled in Maya</MudText>
                    </MudCardContent>
                </MudCard>
            </MudItem>
        </MudGrid>
    </MudStack>
</MudContainer>
